Why RNN's struggle with long-term dependencies ?
RNNs struggle with long-term dependencies because they have difficulty remembering information from many time steps earlier
in a sequence.As sequences become longer, important earlier information gradually gets lost during training
The earlier information gradually fades during training due to the vanishing gradient problem, making it difficult for 
the network to remember important context from far earlier in the sequence.
How LSTM's help with memory ?
LSTMs help with memory by allowing the network to selectively remember important information for a long time and forget
unimportant information.
LSTMs help with memory by using special gates and a cell state to store, update, and preserve important information over long 
sequences, allowing the model to remember long-term context more effectively than simple RNNs.
What attention solves in sequence-to-sequence tasks ?
Attention solves the problem of losing important information in sequence-to-sequence models by allowing the model to focus
on the most relevant parts of the input sequence while generating the output.
It helps the model remember and use important context dynamically.
Attention solves the problem of losing important context in sequence-to-sequence tasks by allowing the model to focus on 
the most relevant parts of the input sequence dynamically while generating each output element.
Why transformers are important in modern NLP and Generative AI ?
Transformers are important in modern NLP and Generative AI because they can understand long-range context, process data 
efficiently, and generate highly accurate human-like text.
They are the foundation of most modern AI systems.
Transformers are important in modern NLP and Generative AI because they efficiently understand long-range context using 
attention mechanisms, enabling powerful applications like chatbots, text generation, translation, and large language 
models such as GPT and BERT.
